<h1><span id="Caro-Kann_Defence:Classical_Variation">Caro-Kann Defence:Classical Variation</span></h1>
<p>The vast majority of times, black plays the solid 3...dxe4, one of the most well-studied of the Caro-Kann lines. Black has alternatives to avoid the weight of theory, although 3...e6, blocking the bishop, and effectively forming a French, with one tempo less, seems a dubious line.
</p>
<p>1.e4 c6 2.d4 d5 3.Nc3
